    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-06-20T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-06-20T16:00:00-05:00" n="108"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d108">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.5/6–2051: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The United States Deputy Representative at the North Atlantic
                        Council</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SCM1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Spofford</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d108fn1">This telegram was repeated to all <gloss
                            target="#t_NATO1">NATO</gloss> capitals and to Frankfurt, Heidelberg,
                        and Wiesbaden.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-06-20T22:00:00+01:00"
                            >June 20, 1951—10 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Depto1">Depto</gloss> 1152. Deputies 48th mtg June 19.</p>
                <p>1. At signature agreement on status <gloss target="#t_NATO1">NAT</gloss> forces
                    UK <gloss target="#t_FonMin1">FonMin</gloss>
                    <persName corresp="#p_MHS1">Morrison</persName> said <gloss target="#t_NATO1"
                        >NATO</gloss> is heart of UK foreign policy. Noted achievements <pb
                        facs="0226" n="188" xml:id="pg_188"/> in organizational phase <gloss
                        target="#t_NATO1">NATO</gloss> and was confident same cooperative spirit wld
                    prevail in solving major problems of production and sharing burden of financing
                    of defense effort now faced. Expressed hope that <gloss target="#t_NATO1"
                        >NATO</gloss>, now primarily concerned with defense, wld lead to even closer
                    association within Atlantic community.<note n="2" xml:id="d108fn2">Regarding the
                        signing of the agreement between the parties of the North Atlantic Treaty
                        regarding the status of armed forces, see the editorial note, <ref
                            target="#pg_186">p. 186</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>2. Resolution on interim application military status agreement adopted.<note
                        n="3" xml:id="d108fn3">The resolution, designated D–D (51) 140, was
                        originally approved by the Council Deputies working group on May 31, and the
                        text was transmitted in telegram <gloss target="#t_Depto1">Depto</gloss>
                        1028, May 31, from London. It stated that some of the provisions of the
                        status-of-forces agreement could be implemented by administrative action
                        without the necessity for legislation and that such implementation would be
                        useful in the period before the agreement was ratified.
                        (740.5/5–3151)</note> Noted French statement that <gloss target="#t_SHAPE1"
                        >SHAPE</gloss> status agreement nearly complete and that similar agreements
                    anticipated for subordinate headquarters.<note n="4" xml:id="d108fn4">Regarding
                        the agreements under reference here, see footnote 8, <ref target="#pg_177"
                            >p. 177</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>[Here follows the remainder of the report on the Council Deputies meeting of June
                    19 which was concerned with a variety of other topics.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SCM1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Spofford</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
